&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time: 18.75 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking to gain experience within the acute adult setting as a Band 5 Dietitian? We are looking for an enthusiastic and forward thinking Dietitian for a Band 5 Part Time Post working within our friendly team which provides Nutrition &amp; Dietetic Services across North Derbyshire&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will gain experience working in a variety of different settings on the acute wards of a busy District General Hospital covering areas including Respiratory, Cardiac, Surgery, Medicine and Haematology and will also have the as opportunity to work with specialist Dietitians in areas such as ITU/HDU, Stroke and Oncology. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Professional Development is encouraged and we provide a supportive preceptorship programme alongside regular structured CPD opportunities. You will join our friendly team of 23 which includes Dietitians, Nutrition Support Nurse, a Dietetic assistant and Admin Support Staff. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be a HCPC registered dietitian with hospital experience.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Chesterfield is geographically well placed for travelling north or south and provides easy access to the motorway network. Temporary accommodation may be available.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post will require a DBS disclosure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMelanie CoyJob titleHead of Nutrition &amp; DieteticsTelephone number01246 512173&lt;/p&gt;
